### Data Quality Control

#### Duplicate Detection
```
Process:
1. Compare title similarity (fuzzy matching)
2. Compare content similarity
3. Check source URL
4. Flag potential duplicates
5. Merge or mark as duplicate

Algorithm:
- Title similarity > 80% = potential duplicate
- Content similarity > 70% = potential duplicate
- Same source URL = duplicate
```

#### Content Validation
```
Checks:
├─ ✓ Has title
├─ ✓ Has content (min 200 words)
├─ ✓ Has source URL
├─ ✓ Has publish date
├─ ✓ Content is readable (not just ads)
└─ ✓ Images are accessible

Invalid Content:
├─ Too short (< 100 words)
├─ Mostly ads/scripts
├─ Broken links
└─ Missing metadata
```

#### Source Attribution
```
Requirements:
├─ Always include source name
├─ Always include source URL
├─ Always include publish date
├─ Add "via [Source]" in metadata
└─ Link back to original (if allowed)

Format:
"Source: CoinDesk | Published: Jan 15, 2024 | Original: [Link]"
```

