### D. API Documentation Reference

#### Research API Endpoints
```
GET /api/research/articles
Query params: source, category, date, search
Returns: List of research articles

GET /api/research/articles/:id
Returns: Single research article

POST /api/research/articles/:id/save
Saves article for research
Requires: Authentication
```

#### Content API Endpoints
```
GET /api/articles
Query params: page, limit, category, search, sort
Returns: List of published articles

GET /api/articles/:slug
Returns: Single article

GET /api/categories
Returns: All categories with article counts

GET /api/search?q=query
Returns: Search results
```

### E. Database Schema Reference

#### Articles Table
```sql
CREATE TABLE articles (
  id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  title VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
  slug VARCHAR(255) UNIQUE NOT NULL,
  content TEXT NOT NULL,
  excerpt TEXT,
  category VARCHAR(50),
  tags TEXT[],
  featured_image VARCHAR(255),
  author_id INTEGER,
  status VARCHAR(20) DEFAULT 'draft',
  published_at TIMESTAMP,
  created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW(),
  updated_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW(),
  meta_title VARCHAR(255),
  meta_description TEXT,
  seo_keywords TEXT[]
);
```

#### Research Articles Table
```sql
CREATE TABLE research_articles (
  id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  source VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
  source_url VARCHAR(500) NOT NULL,
  title VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
  content TEXT NOT NULL,
  summary TEXT,
  category VARCHAR(50),
  tags TEXT[],
  published_date TIMESTAMP,
  collected_date TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW(),
  status VARCHAR(20) DEFAULT 'research',
  key_points JSONB,
  sentiment VARCHAR(20)
);
```

